**@SubscriptionMapping in Spring for GraphQL:**

```java
@Controller
public class ZerodhaSubscriptionController {

    // Publishes live price updates as a Reactor Flux:
    @SubscriptionMapping
    public Flux<PriceUpdate> priceUpdate(@Argument String symbol) {
        return Flux.interval(Duration.ofSeconds(1)) // tick every second
            .map(tick -> fetchCurrentPrice(symbol))
            .filter(update -> update.price() > 0)  // filter out bad data
            .onBackpressureDrop()  // drop slow consumer overflow
            .doOnCancel(() -> log.info("Client {} unsubscribed from {}", symbol));
    }

    // Payment status: push updates until CAPTURED or FAILED:
    @SubscriptionMapping
    public Flux<PaymentStatus> paymentStatus(@Argument String paymentId) {
        return paymentUpdatePublisher
            .asFlux()
            .filter(status -> status.paymentId().equals(paymentId))
            .takeUntil(status -> status.isFinal()); // stop after terminal state
    }
}
```

